urth and final printed work."},{"number":2,"category":"death","header":"A Latin stone, translated for the curious","body":"His Milford monument, in Latin, credits him with honors from both Yale and Harvard and “virtues, piety and good deeds” that “everywhere shone with peculiar lustre” across more than thirty years in the town’s pulpit."}],"slug":"samuel-whittlesey-1713"},"H00142":{"id":"H00142","has_descendants_documented":true,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"generation_from_thomas":5,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1716,"month":1,"day":14},"death":{"year":1803,"month":5,"day":9,"city":"Middletown","state":"Connecticut"},"marriages":[{"spouse_id":"I00020","children_ids":["HD0097","HD0098","HD0099","HD0100"],"marriage_number":1,"end_type":"death_of_spouse","end_year":1768,"date_year":1743,"date_month":9,"date_day":2},{"children_ids":[],"spouse_id":"X01007","marriage_number":2,"date_year":1771,"date_month":9,"date_day":21}],"parents":{"father_id":"H00044","mother_id":"I00013"},"tags":[],"sources":[{"short":"Edward Hooker 1909","page":"Entry 142"},{"short":"Whittlesey Genealogy","notes":"Children confirmed; character description preserved"}],"gender":"female","number_of_marriages":2,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[{"type":"in_law","related_id":"X01900","display_label":"was her father-in-law"}],"bio":{"display_name":"Susannah Newton Hamlin","first_name":"Susannah","last_name":"Hamlin","married_names":["Whittlesey","Hamlin"],"maiden_name":"Newton"},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"narrative_blocks":[{"number":1,"category":"marriage","header":"Married Milford minister, then Middletown statesman","body":"Her first husband Rev. Samuel Whittlesey served Milford for thirty-plus years until his death in 1768. She remarried Hon. Jabez Hamlin of Middletown — described as 'distinguished in civil and military life.'"},{"number":2,"category":"character","header":"Whittlesey genealogy: 'lady of high intellectual qualities'","body":"The Whittlesey genealogy describes her as 'a lady of high intellectual and moral qualities.' This was an unusual tribute for a colonial woman, whose lives were typically invisible in family records of the era."},{"number":3,"category":"death","header":"Outlived both husbands; died at 87 in Middletown","body":"She outlived her first husband Rev. Samuel Whittlesey by 35 years and her second husband Jabez Hamlin as well. She died at Middletown in 1803, age 87."}],"slug":"susannah-hamlin-1716"},"X00078":{"id":"X00078","classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":false,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"birth":{"year":1717},"death":{"year":1790,"month":3,"day":21},"marriages":[{"children_ids":[],"spouse_id":"X01838","marriage_number":1,"end_type":"death_of_spouse","date_year":1741,"date_month":12,"date_day":31,"location_city":"Litchfield","location_state":"Connecticut"},{"children_ids":["I00075"],"spouse_id":"X01839","marriage_number":2,"date_year":1755,"date_month":5,"date_day":22}],"sources":[],"gender":"male","tags":[],"number_of_marriages":2,"parents":{},"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Jacob Woodruff","first_name":"Jacob","last_name":"Woodruff","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"jacob-woodruff-1717"},"X01839":{"id":"X01839","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":f